Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for React Application

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the React job portal application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package version 1.6.1 using yarn
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `yarn.lock` to reflect the new package and its dependencies

### 2. Code Integration
Modified `src/App.js`:
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `App` function, placed within the `ThemeProvider` wrapper but outside the `BrowserRouter` to ensure proper tracking
- The Analytics component is positioned at the end of the component tree to ensure it doesn't interfere with existing functionality

## Implementation Details
- The `<Analytics />` component was placed inside the `ThemeProvider` but after the `BrowserRouter` closes, following React component composition best practices
- This placement ensures analytics tracking is initialized properly while maintaining the existing application structure
- No route-specific configuration was added as this is a plain React (Create React App) implementation

## Verification
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Production build created without issues (190.28 kB main JS bundle)
✅ All existing functionality preserved
✅ Lock files properly updated

## Files Modified
- `src/App.js` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `yarn.lock` - Updated with new package dependencies

The implementation follows the project's existing code patterns and maintains compatibility with the current React 19 and Create React App 5 setup.
